---
import { Image } from 'astro:assets';
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import CTA from '../components/CTA.astro';
import { business } from '../data/business';

import heroImg from '../assets/images/misc/3.jpg';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Your Pet's Experience | Healthy Paws Animal Hospital"
  description="Experience exceptional pet care at Healthy Paws with personalized attention, stress-free visits, and innovative practices for happy, healthy furry companions in Lake in the Hills, IL."
>
  <!-- Hero Banner -->
  <section class="hero-banner">
    <div class="absolute inset-0">
      <Image
        src={heroImg}
        alt="A dog standing on its hind legs at Healthy Paws Animal Hospital"
        class="w-full h-full object-cover"
        loading="eager"
        widths={[640, 960, 1280, 1920]}
      />
      <div class="absolute inset-0" style="background: rgba(0,0,0,0.4);"></div>
    </div>
    <div class="container relative z-10 text-center">
      <h1 class="text-4xl lg:text-5xl text-white mb-4">Your Pet's Experience</h1>
      <p class="text-lg text-white/90 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
        Experience exceptional pet care at <a href="/about/" class="text-white underline">Healthy Paws</a> with personalized attention, stress-free visits, and innovative practices for happy, healthy furry companions.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Quote -->
  <section class="py-12" style="background-color: #DEDEE9;">
    <div class="container text-center" style="max-width: 700px;">
      <p class="text-lg text-hpah-text leading-relaxed italic">
        "Be brave. Take risks. Nothing can substitute experience."
      </p>
      <p class="font-bold mt-3">Paulo Coelho</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Main Content -->
  <section class="py-16 lg:py-20">
    <div class="container" style="max-width: 900px;">
      <h2 class="text-3xl mb-6">Exam Room Experience</h2>

      <p class="mb-6 leading-relaxed">
        How would I like to be treated, and what would annoy me if I were taking my sick pet to the <a href="/meet-the-team/">veterinarian</a>? Working in the veterinary field since the age of fourteen has afforded me the opportunity to see many examples of the good and the bad. When building our practice, countless people told us "you can't" along the way. We are proud of how we challenged these, at times, archaic, traditional veterinary office ideas to create a better experience for our clients and patients.
      </p>

      <p class="mb-6 leading-relaxed">
        Our exam room experience begins before our clients step through the front door. We work aggressively to schedule appointments mindfully, choosing exam rooms based on client or patient needs. On arrival, pets are greeted, weighed, and escorted immediately to their exam room. The concept of sitting in a confined space while my pet is stressed with furry and human strangers surrounding us has always baffled me. Our lobby is small for this reason, for show only, and we consider it a failure if you spend significant time there.
      </p>

      <p class="mb-6 leading-relaxed">
        In the exam room, clients are partnered with a team member for their visit. This team member completes a medical history and puts together a tentative treatment plan, including financial options. After the <a href="/meet-the-team/">veterinarian</a>'s examination and discussion, this same team member completes all agreed-upon diagnostics and procedures, prepares any necessary prescriptions, and goes over the final treatment plan.
      </p>

      <p class="mb-6 leading-relaxed">
        At the conclusion of a visit, clients are checked out in the privacy of their exam room. There are no surprises, no public discussion of finances, and no worrying about a dog tugging on a leash or a cat being terrified while paying a bill.
      </p>

      <p class="mb-6 leading-relaxed">
        There are other unique attributes to a <a href="/about/">Healthy Paws</a> visit. Our floor-to-ceiling exam room windows allow pets a welcome diversion during their visit. Having the flexibility to examine pets on a padded table, on the floor, or in the lobby gives us many options to help alleviate anxiety. A myriad of treats allow pets to choose between salty, sweet, crunchy, and chewy. And pheromone diffusers (synthetic scents) help calm our feline friends.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <CTA heading="Experience the Difference" text="Schedule a visit and see what veterinary care looks like when it's built around your pet's comfort." />
</BaseLayout>
